com.github.zk1931.jzab

Class Zab

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.zk1931.jzab.Zab

  • public class Zab
extends Object
    Quorum zab implementation. This class manages the quorum zab servers. For each server, it can be in one of three states : ELECTING, FOLLOWING, LEADING. Among all the nodes, there's only one server can be established leader.

      • send

        public void send(ByteBuffer request)
          throws ZabException.NotBroadcastingPhaseException
        Submits a request to Zab. Any one can call call this send. Under the hood, followers forward requests to the leader and the leader will be responsible for converting this request to idempotent transaction and broadcasting. If you send request in non-broadcasting phase, the operation will fail.
        Parameters:
        request - request to send through Zab
        Throws:
        ZabException.NotBroadcastingPhaseException - if Zab is not in broadcasting phase.

      • flush

        public void flush(ByteBuffer request)
           throws ZabException.NotBroadcastingPhaseException
        Flushes a request through pipeline. The flushed request will be delivered in order with other sending requests, but it will not be convereted to idempotent transaction and will not be persisted in log. And it will only be delivered on the server who issued this request. The purpose of flush is to allow implementing a consistent read-after-write. If you send flush request in non-broadcasting phase, the operation will fail.
        Parameters:
        request - the request to be flushed.
        Throws:
        ZabException.NotBroadcastingPhaseException - if Zab is not in broadcasting phase.

      • remove

        public void remove(String peerId)
            throws ZabException.NotBroadcastingPhaseException
        Removes a peer from the cluster. If you send remove request in non-broadcasting phase, the operation will fail.
        Parameters:
        peerId - the id of the peer who will be removed from the cluster.
        Throws:
        ZabException.NotBroadcastingPhaseException - if Zab is not in broadcasting phase.
